               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t16870701-17-defend89" type="defendantName">
                  Sarah 
                  Bourrus
               <interp inst="t16870701-17-defend89" type="surname" value="Bourrus"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16870701-17-defend89" type="given" value="Sarah"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16870701-17-defend89" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             of the Parish of <placeName id="t16870701-17-defloc76">St. Giles's Criplegate</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t16870701-17-defloc76" type="placeName" value="St. Giles's Criplegate"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t16870701-17-defloc76" type="type" value="defendantHome"></interp>
                  <join result="persNamePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t16870701-17-defend89 t16870701-17-defloc76"></join>, was tryed for <rs id="t16870701-17-off77" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16870701-17-off77" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16870701-17-off77" type="offenceSubcategory" value="shoplifting"></interp>
               stealing three pair of Shooes from 
                     
                        <persName id="t16870701-17-victim91" type="victimName">
                           George 
                           Powel
                        <interp inst="t16870701-17-victim91" type="surname" value="Powel"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t16870701-17-victim91" type="given" value="George"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t16870701-17-victim91" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t16870701-17-off77 t16870701-17-victim91"></join>
                     </persName>
                     
                  ; the proof was, that coming into the Shop of the prosecutor to cheapen a pair of Shooes, and not agreeing upon the price, Two pair of Shooes upon their departure were missing
            </rs>, and upon pursuit found in a Basket that the Prisoner had upon her Arm, to which she pleaded, that she knew not that they were there, but that a Woman who Accompanied her, gave it her to carry, yet no such thing appearing any other ways than by her own Testimony, she was found <rs id="t16870701-17-verdict78" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16870701-17-verdict78" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16870701-17-verdict78" type="verdictSubcategory" value="theftunder1s"></interp>
               Guilty to the value of 10 d.
            </rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t16870701-17-punish79" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t16870701-17-punish79" type="punishmentCategory" value="corporal"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t16870701-17-punish79" type="punishmentSubcategory" value="whipping"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t16870701-17-defend89 t16870701-17-punish79"></join>
               
                     <note>[Whipping. See summary.]</note>
               
                  </rs>
               </p>
